psalm.text:
[[Ps 31,2]]In you, O LORD, I take refuge; 
let me never be put to shame. 
In your justice rescue me,
[[Ps 31,6]]Into your hands I commend my spirit; 
You will redeem me, O LORD, O faithful God.

[[Ps 31,12]]For all my foes I am an object of reproach, 
a laughingstock to my neighbors, and a dread to my friends; 
they who see me abroad flee from me.
[[Ps 31,13]]I am forgotten like the unremembered dead; 
I am like a dish that is broken.

[[Ps 31,15]]But my trust is in you, O LORD; 
I say, "You are my God.
[[Ps 31,16]]In your hands is my destiny; rescue me 
from the clutches of my enemies and my persecutors."

[[Ps 31,17]]Let your face shine upon your servant; 
save me in your kindness.
[[Ps 31,25]]Take courage and be stouthearted,
all you who hope in the LORD.
